    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean i know i should talk to them but they never listen and just tell me to keep eating the same boring stuff. i read online that garlic is actually a super strong natural blood thinner and if i take enough of it it might do the same thing as the pills. do u think if i just took like 3-4 thousand mg of garlic extract a day i could probably get away with skipping the warfarin for a while? i just want to feel like i have some control over my own body again.",
